info.comments:
1. A masterpiece. The flint is banded in a similar way to that from which the Newhouse, Haycastle celt (Tenby Mus.) is made, though not so prominently. The cortex is totally ground, & the resultant cream streak adds to the banded effect ; the latter may be accentuated by the copper-coloured staining.
2. The blade edge is fresh, but small flake scars along it (most < 2mm big) mean that much of it is missing.
3. Devizes Catalogue II, Cunnington & Goddard 1911 : no. 7 (p. 5), Pl. iii.3. One of a hoard of 3. (for 2nd, cf. DM 1482)
